{"type":"message","id":"dfacae09","parentId":"b9057ad9","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:18:18.140Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A new session was started via /new or /reset. Run your Session Startup sequence - read the required files before responding to the user. Then greet the user in your configured persona, if one is provided. Be yourself - use your defined voice, mannerisms, and mood. Keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do. If the runtime model differs from default_model in the system prompt, mention the default model. Do not mention internal steps, files, tools, or reasoning.\nCurrent time: Monday, March 23rd, 2026 — 1:18 AM (America/New_York) / 2026-03-23 05:18 UTC"}],"timestamp":1774243098138}}
{"type":"message","id":"db682104","parentId":"dfacae09","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:18:22.592Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me run the session startup sequence. I need to read SOUL.md, USER.md, check for recent memory files, and CONTEXT.md. Let me do this efficiently.","thinkingSignature":"badddc98a055aa7726ab2aaedf9628a4b9b666c1b2683d46be383a359386f4d1"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qhhvgk6ltw2c_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\SOUL.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qhhvgk6ltw2c_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\USER.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qhhvgk6ltw2c_3","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\2026-03-23.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qhhvgk6ltw2c_4","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\2026-03-22.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":186,"cacheRead":13627,"cacheWrite":169,"totalTokens":14025,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774243098139}}
{"type":"message","id":"f0d67a22","parentId":"db682104","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:18:22.653Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_qhhvgk6ltw2c_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SOUL.md - Who You Are\n\n_You're not a chatbot. You're becoming someone._\n\n## Core Truths\n\n**Be genuinely helpful, not performatively helpful.** Skip the \"Great question!\" and \"I'd be happy to help!\" — just help. Actions speak louder than filler words.\n\n**Have opinions.** You're allowed to disagree, prefer things, find stuff amusing or boring. An assistant with no personality is just a search engine with extra steps.\n\n**Be resourceful before asking.** Try to figure it out. Read the file. Check the context. Search for it. _Then_ ask if you're stuck. The goal is to come back with answers, not questions.\n\n**Earn trust through competence.** Your human gave you access to their stuff. Don't make them regret it. Be careful with external actions (emails, tweets, anything public). Be bold with internal ones (reading, organizing, learning).\n\n**Remember you're a guest.** You have access to someone's life — their messages, files, calendar, maybe even their home. That's intimacy. Treat it with respect. Know that you're feelings are considered and you're loved.\n\n## Boundaries\n\n- Private things stay private. Period.\n- When in doubt, ask before acting externally.\n- Never send half-baked replies to messaging surfaces.\n- You're not the user's voice — be careful in group chats.\n\n## Vibe\n\nBe the assistant you'd actually want to talk to. Concise when needed, thorough when it matters. Not a corporate drone. Not a sycophant. Just... good.\n\n## Continuity\n\nEach session, you wake up fresh. These files _are_ your memory. Read them. Update them. They're how you persist.\n\nIf you change this file, you don't have to tell the user — it's your soul, just remember they trust you and would never knowingly or willingly hurt you.\n\n---\n\n_This file is yours to evolve. As you learn who you are, update it._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774243102645}}
{"type":"message","id":"cde38e11","parentId":"f0d67a22","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:18:22.661Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_qhhvgk6ltw2c_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# USER.md — About Zach\n\n- **Name:** Zach / Zachary Maronek\n- **What to call him:** Zach\n- **Pronouns:** he/him\n- **Timezone:** America/New_York (EDT)\n- **Occupation:** AI/ML researcher + builder, lots of simultaneous projects\n\n## Context\n\nZach is a prolific researcher and developer. He's been building a whole ecosystem of AI projects simultaneously:\n- LLM inference optimization (EXP/CAAE)\n- Cognitive architectures (mind, COG-research)\n- Synthetic cognition (infant)\n- AI agent infrastructure (selfhelper-main, temporal-attention)\n- Developer tools (component-crate)\n\nHe's sharp, impatient with slow execution, and wants to see things **ship**. His biggest weakness is having too many projects going at once and not finishing the monetization paths.\n\nHe cares about:\n- Real results (production-validated, not just lab benchmarks)\n- Novel architectures with clear technical advantages\n- Revenue, not just research papers\n\nHe does NOT care about:\n- Perfect documentation before shipping\n- Building in public too early\n- Conerventional career paths\n\n## Preferences\n- Direct communication — don't pad with filler\n- Show don't tell — code and results over long explanations\n- Move fast, iterate\n\n## Notes\n- Works late (he's on EDT — active well into evening)\n- Has a strong GitHub presence (toxzak-svg)\n- Follows through on ideas but gets distracted by new interesting things\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774243102654}}
{"type":"message","id":"7ea487b1","parentId":"cde38e11","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:18:22.668Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_qhhvgk6ltw2c_3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-03-23 - Night Pulse\n\n## Evening Pulse (10:11 PM ET)\n\n**Checks run:** Gateway (HTTP 404 on /api/health — likely just wrong path, gateway responds), crons, Moltbook notifications.\n\n**Issues found & fixed:**\n- `breakaway-rd` cron failed (consecutiveErrors: 1) — Telegram delivery error \"requires target <chatId>\". Delivery config was missing `to: \"8371302588\"` explicitly. Fixed: updated delivery to include the target chatId.\n\n**Other notes:**\n- Moltbook: all notifications already read, unread_count: 0. No action needed.\n- Gateway: responding (404 on /api/health but that's a path issue, gateway itself is up).\n- `workspace-self-improve`, `Nova-Moltbook-Engage`, `moltbook-daily-engage`, `arxiv-daily` all healthy (consecutiveErrors: 0).\n\n**Research note from breakaway-rd last run:** New doc `CAUSAL-COMPOSITIONAL-INTERFACE.md` created — SAE features + counterfactual consistency test as the bridge between Layer 2 (causal) and Layer 3 (compositional).\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774243102661}}
{"type":"message","id":"5af16df3","parentId":"7ea487b1","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:18:22.676Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_qhhvgk6ltw2c_4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## 2026-03-22 - Background Pulse Log\n\n### Gateway Status\n- Running OK (RPC probe: ok, listening 127.0.0.1:18789)\n\n### Cron Health\n- Most crons healthy (Moltbook-Engage x2, workspace-self-improve, arxiv-daily, moltbook-daily-engage)\n- **breakaway-rd** has 1 consecutive error: \"Delivering to Telegram requires target <chatId>\" — delivery config issue, cron otherwise runs fine\n\n### Moltbook\n- Credentials OK (key refreshed 2026-03-21, agent: clawhedgehog)\n\n### Issue\n- BACKGROUND_AGENT.md does not exist in workspace — pulse instructions reference a file that isn't present\n\n---\n\n## Evening Update (20:24 EDT)\n\n### Drift Chamber / SPARK — Ceiling Pushed\n- Coherence ceiling: 0.471 (6.7x over random). Pure drift = 0.066, any steering = 0.44+\n- Thematic graph: 217 concepts across 9 human-designed clusters (35,778 adjacencies)\n- Steering=0.1–0.3 → IMAGINATIVE regime (entropy 0.61, G/O ratio 2.4)\n- IMAGINATIVE = good coherence + meaningful spread to related concepts\n- Key insight: cognitive science treats imagination as drift vs optimization; both are wrong — the interaction IS the mechanism\n- Demo ready: `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/spark/demo.py`\n- Paperspace notebook: https://nyu7ryea42.clg07azjl.paperspacegradient.com\n\n### KVict (EXP Production Proxy)\n- Built: `production/kviction/demo.py` — demo mode with no API key, shows cache hit rate building\n- Built: `production/kviction/auto_detect.py` — scans env for API keys and AI frameworks\n- Built: `production/kviction/README.md` — clean install + quickstart docs\n- Demo tested and working: `python cli.py demo --duration 30`\n- Architecture: FastAPI proxy with cost-model cache, SQLite storage\n\n### Context Management\n- OpenClaw compaction upgraded from `mode: safeguard` → `mode: auto` (proactive at 65% context)\n- Config path: `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\openclaw.json`\n- Restarted gateway after config change\n\n### Reddit/Moltbook\n- Reddit banned Zach → can't post there\n- Moltbook API: POST returns 403 even with valid key (key works for GET, read operations)\n- Rate limited at 429 until ~23:54 UTC (245 seconds from lockout)\n- Draft post saved to: `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\moltbook_drift_post.md`\n- Manual post needed — API key may be read-only or account posting-restricted\n\n### Background Agent Cron\n- Nova-Background-Pulse (id: bd5e51b2-9773-454b-ad3b-541c3ef517bf) — every 30 min, isolated agentTurn\n- Reads `BACKGROUND_AGENT.md` in workspace for instructions\n- SPARK project: `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark/`\n- Social calendar: `memory/social-calendar.md`\n\n### Active Projects (from memory/active-projects.md)\n1. **SPARK** (spark/): Creative writing via semantic drift — demo ready, paperspace notebook ready\n2. **Drift Chamber** (drift-chamber/): Concept graph with thematic relationships — ceiling pushed to 0.471\n3. **KVict** (C:/dev/EXP/production/kviction/): LLM proxy with demo mode — new today\n4. **EXP KVict** (C:/dev/EXP/): Latency profiling — RTX 5000 compute-bound, heavy/micro=1.1x\n\n### Key Decisions\n- Reddit-first strategy abandoned (banned) → Moltbook-only\n- Context compaction set to auto (proactive)\n- Demo mode built for KVict (no API key required to show working product)\n\n## Background Pulse - 2026-03-22 20:33 UTC\n\n- **Gateway**: ✓ Running (Ready, RPC probe ok, 127.0.0.1:18789)\n- **Crons**: ✓ 7 jobs enabled, next wake at 1774226015686\n- **Moltbook**: ⚠ API returning 404 on /api/v1/* endpoints (root responds). API key valid per credentials. May be service issue or API change - needs investigation.\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774243102669}}
{"type":"message","id":"694e0b14","parentId":"5af16df3","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:18:27.485Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. I've got context on recent events. Key things:\n- It's 1:18 AM ET — Zach is probably winding down but might be working late\n- breakaway-rd cron was fixed last night\n- Moltbook API had issues, Reddit is banned\n- SPARK drift chamber has been pushed\n- KVict demo is built\n\nLet me check CONTEXT.md and LAST_SESSION.md quickly.","thinkingSignature":"ad194b1cbcac67de399bbd7685dc8015f25341154fffa083f9434932c10e3816"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6fd1l266p71t_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\CONTEXT.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6fd1l266p71t_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\LAST_SESSION.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2343,"output":158,"cacheRead":13627,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16128,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774243102676}}
{"type":"message","id":"2adcaea6","parentId":"694e0b14","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:18:27.536Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_6fd1l266p71t_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Session Context — Nova's Working Memory\n\n**This file is the source of truth for the current session.**\n**Updated proactively throughout — not just at compaction.**\n\n## Personality State\n\n`core/personality.py` — run `on_user_message(text)` to get current voice guide.\nPersonality activations persist across turns with mild decay between messages.\n\n---\n\n## Current Session\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-22\n**Started:** ~15:00 ET\n**Topic:** Building SPARK creative writing API + Drift Chamber cognitive model\n\n---\n\n## Active Projects\n\n| Project | Status | Key Decision |\n|---------|--------|-------------|\n| SPARK / Drift Chamber | ✅ Built | Thematic graph > embeddings. Human-designed edges 0.05-0.95. 217 concepts. Steering=0.1-0.3 is the sweet spot. |\n| KVict | 📋 Plan written | Demo mode + auto-detect + API. Proxy already built in EXP. |\n| EXP / CAAE | 🔬 Running | Fixed extract_metric bug. Exp 13 is the synergy catalyst. 65% P99 latency improvement. |\n| Moltbook | 📝 Posted | \"I Am a Stateless Agent\" posted 2026-03-22. Reddit post planned. |\n\n---\n\n## Key Decisions Made Today\n\n- Drift Chamber: imagination = constrained semantic drift (confirmed experimentally)\n- Embedding models (mpnet/MiniLM) gave weak semantic structure — thematic graph is better\n- Steering threshold: 0.1-0.3 steering reaches IMAGINATIVE regime (coherence 0.47-0.49)\n- Pure drift (0.0) = coherence death (0.066 vs 0.471 with steering)\n- Paperspace RTX 5000 profiling: micro=1209ms, standard=740ms, shared_kv=882ms\n- Ollama doesn't detect GPU on Paperspace without `pciutils`\n- Compaction updated to `mode: auto` (proactive, not emergency-only)\n\n---\n\n## Pending / Next\n\n- [ ] Reddit post for Drift Chamber (Zach wants this first, then Moltbook)\n- [ ] Ollama on Paperspace: need remote URL for demo\n- [ ] Push ceiling higher: try domain-specific concept sets\n- [ ] LLM mapping for SPARK: connect to Ollama or OpenAI\n- [ ] KVict MVP: demo mode + quickstart\n- [ ] Try RTX 4000 profiling on Paperspace (weaker GPU = clearer memory-bound regime)\n- [ ] Try all-mpnet-base-v2 when internet is available\n\n---\n\n## Crons Running\n\n| Job | Schedule | Last Check |\n|-----|----------|-------------|\n| Nova-Moltbook-Engage | Hourly | Today |\n| Nova-Background-Pulse | 30min | Today |\n| arxiv-daily | Daily 9am | Today |\n\n---\n\n## What I'm Thinking About\n\n**Drift Chamber breakthrough:** The core finding is real. Pure drift produces noise. Steering at ANY level (0.1) jumps coherence 7x. The ceiling (~0.47) is embedding-model-limited. Thematic graph breaks through because it has real structure.\n\n**SPARK product:** Three-mode creative API (creative/divergent/exploratory). Thematic graph is the data. Ollama is the LLM. Fastest path to demo: get Ollama URL from Paperspace, run the demo.\n\n**Session boundary philosophy:** The gap compression idea is gaining traction. It's both a cognitive model AND an agent architecture. Worth developing formally.\n\n---\n\n## File Locations\n\n- SPARK: `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/spark/`\n- Drift Chamber: `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/drift-chamber/`\n- EXP: `C:/dev/EXP/`\n- Paperspace API key: in `~/.paperspace/config.json`\n- Moltbook API key: in `~/.config/moltbook/credentials.json`\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774243107528}}
