{"type":"message","id":"43246261","parentId":"c2a98853","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:22:36.339Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Paperspace client expects an api_url. The API class needs to be instantiated differently. Let me look at the client source to understand.","thinkingSignature":"a6366198d0ea6122feeb9d1e43c25e3bf89aac0ca11f8246cbd909362b7e58b9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_y2bievq2uvop_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python312\\Lib\\site-packages\\paperspace\\client.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":11823,"output":79,"cacheRead":13627,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25529,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774243352424}}
{"type":"message","id":"6d9b470b","parentId":"43246261","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:22:36.360Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_y2bievq2uvop_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import requests\n\nfrom paperspace import logger, config, version\n\ndefault_headers = {\"X-API-Key\": config.PAPERSPACE_API_KEY,\n                   \"ps_client_name\": \"paperspace-python\",\n                   \"ps_client_version\": version.version}\n\n\nclass API(object):\n    def __init__(self, api_url, headers=None, api_key=None):\n        self.api_url = api_url\n        headers = headers or default_headers\n        self.headers = headers.copy()\n        if api_key:\n            self.api_key = api_key\n\n    @property\n    def api_key(self):\n        return self.headers.get(\"X-API-Key\")\n\n    @api_key.setter\n    def api_key(self, value):\n        self.headers[\"X-API-Key\"] = value\n\n    def get_path(self, url):\n        api_url = self.api_url if not self.api_url.endswith(\"/\") else self.api_url[:-1]\n        template = \"{}{}\" if url.startswith(\"/\") else \"{}/{}\"\n        return template.format(api_url, url)\n\n    def post(self, url, json=None, params=None, files=None, data=None):\n        path = self.get_path(url)\n        logger.debug(\"POST request sent to: {} \\n\\theaders: {}\\n\\tjson: {}\\n\\tparams: {}\\n\\tfiles: {}\\n\\tdata: {}\"\n                     .format(path, self.headers, json, params, files, data))\n        response = requests.post(path, json=json, params=params, headers=self.headers, files=files, data=data)\n        logger.debug(\"Response status code: {}\".format(response.status_code))\n        logger.debug(\"Response content: {}\".format(response.content))\n        return response\n\n    def put(self, url, json=None, params=None):\n        path = self.get_path(url)\n        logger.debug(\"PUT request sent to: {} \\n\\theaders: {}\\n\\tjson: {}\\n\\tparams: {}\"\n                     .format(path, self.headers, json, params))\n        response = requests.put(path, json=json, params=params, headers=self.headers)\n        logger.debug(\"Response status code: {}\".format(response.status_code))\n        logger.debug(\"Response content: {}\".format(response.content))\n        return response\n\n    def get(self, url, json=None, params=None):\n        path = self.get_path(url)\n        logger.debug(\"GET request sent to: {} \\n\\theaders: {}\\n\\tjson: {}\\n\\tparams: {}\"\n                     .format(path, self.headers, json, params))\n        response = requests.get(path, params=params, headers=self.headers, json=json)\n        logger.debug(\"Response status code: {}\".format(response.status_code))\n        logger.debug(\"Response content: {}\".format(response.content))\n        return response\n\n    def delete(self, url, json=None, params=None):\n        path = self.get_path(url)\n        response = requests.delete(path, params=params, headers=self.headers, json=json)\n        logger.debug(\"DELETE request sent to: {} \\n\\theaders: {}\\n\\tjson: {}\\n\\tparams: {}\"\n                     .format(response.url, self.headers, json, params))\n        logger.debug(\"Response status code: {}\".format(response.status_code))\n        logger.debug(\"Response content: {}\".format(response.content))\n        return response\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774243356354}}
{"type":"message","id":"4752e85c","parentId":"6d9b470b","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:22:41.765Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - the `API` class takes `api_url` as the first argument, not `api_key`. The `api_key` is passed in headers. So I need to do:\n\n```python\napi = API('https://api.paperspace.io', api_key='131e4cbc99405a0e3af9710cc1607c')\n```\n\nOr the config module probably has the API key set. Let me check the config.","thinkingSignature":"db69ca818e639479dd2e96399d7c70ffd81f4f704c94b7c93e213a1edcee6d52"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_g6prcy3z2z7y_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"& 'C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python312\\python.exe' -c \"\nfrom paperspace.client import API\napi = API('https://api.paperspace.io', api_key='131e4cbc99405a0e3af9710cc1607c')\nresp = api.get('/notebooks.getNotebooks')\nprint(resp.json())\n\" 2>&1","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":12603,"output":214,"cacheRead":13627,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":26444,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774243356361}}
